isoiec80000:term-t10-83.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "dose equivalent"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t10-83.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "H"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t10-83.1 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "10-83.1" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t10-83.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t10-83.1-0 ;
  skos:definition """product of the absorbed dose stem:[D] (<<t10-81.1>>) to tissue at the point of interest and the quality factor stem:[Q] (<<t10-82>>) at that point:

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
H = DQ
++++
"""@en ;
  skos:note """The sievert (stem:[\"unitsml(Sv)\"]) is a special name for joule per kilogram, and is the coherent SI unit for dose equivalent.

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
1 \"unitsml(Sv)\" = 1 \"unitsml(J/kg)\"
++++

The dose equivalent at a point in tissue is given by:

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
H = int_0^(oo) Q(L)D_L \"d\"L
++++

where stem:[D_L = \"d\"D//\"d\"L] is the distribution of stem:[D] in stem:[L] at the point of interest. See <<icrp>>.

The quantities measured with radiation protection dosimeters are based on the definition stem:[H = Q D]. If various radiation qualities stem:[i] have to be simultaneously accounted for, the definition is:

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
H = sum_i Q_i D_i.
++++

In ICRU 51 this quantity is denoted as \"dose equivalent\".

In order to quantify the radiation exposition of the human body and to specify dose limits, use is made of a quantity defined in ICRP 103, the \"equivalent dose to a tissue or organ\": stem:[H_\"T\" = w_\"T\" sum_\"R\" w_\"R\" D_\"T,R\"]. The weighting factors stem:[w_\"T\"] for various tissues and organs stem:[T] and stem:[w_\"R\"] for various radiation qualities stem:[\"R\"] have been numerically laid down in ICRP 103. stem:[D_\"T,R\"] is the mean absorbed dose to tissue within a tissue or organ stem:[\"T\"], imparted by radiation with radiation quality stem:[\"R\"].
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-Sv ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-J/kg ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-m^2*s^(-2) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-10 .